<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="TSJN-01-05-0485-sn">
<p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ recipient's copy ]">RC</abbr> (<span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Library of Virginia, Richmond ]">Vi</span>); endorsed. The enclosed account is on a separate page of Clays letter.</p>
<p><a id="TSJN-01-05-0485-kw-0001" class="keywordref" title="jump to Bills  in favour of Mr. Morgan Brown in text" href="#TSJN-01-05-0485-ks-0001">Bills  in favour of Mr. Morgan Brown</a>: On 17 Apr. the Council took the following action: The Auditors are directed to issue to Morgan Brown or order two warrants for thirty two thousand two hundred and fifty Dollars each as of Joseph Clays Draughts, provided that the whole of the President of Congresss warrant of the 16th March 1780  be not already paid (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;Journals of the Council of the State of Virginia&lt;/i&gt;, ed. H. R. McIlwaine ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Va. Council Jour.</span></span>, <span class="hi-small-caps" style="font-variant: small-caps;">ii</span>, 336).</p></div>
